            . On the 2nd of March I was in <placeName id="t18320405-43-crimeloc282">Upper St. Martin's-lane</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18320405-43-crimeloc282" type="placeName" value="Upper St. Martin's-lane"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18320405-43-crimeloc282" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18320405-43-off280 t18320405-43-crimeloc282"></join>, between half-past four and a quarter to five o'clock - I felt something; I disengaged my hand from my brother, and felt my pocket - I missed my handkerchief; I saw the prisoner and another man in conversation, on the opposite side of the way - they then separated; the prisoner was going off - I went towards him, and he threw down this handkerchief; I took him, and a gentleman took the handkerchief.</p>
               <p>Cross-examined. Q. You did not see him take it? A. No - I have inquired, and find his father is a respectable man.</p>
               <p>The prisoner received a good character.</p>
               <p>GUILTY. Aged 16.</p>
